CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 19, 1954, pg. 26, reads: "Archie Moore and 'Double' - While World Light-heavyweight Champion Archie Moore visited the Courier establishment last week, he met in Courier employe [employee] Dyke Bankston (center) a well nigh perfect duplication of self.  The two men looked at each other rather quizzically before breaking forth in loud, horse-laughter.  Posing with them (at right) is Tiger Bland, a member of Moore's stable."
TitMainTitle: Boxer Archie Moore, Pittsburgh Courier newspaper employee Dyke Bankston, and Tiger Bland standing in front of Courier offices, Centre Avenue, Hill District
